        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(channels): clear registry-lookup cache in resetPluginRuntimeStateForTest",
        "body": "## Summary\r\n\r\n`resetPluginRuntimeStateForTest()` clears multiple runtime singletons and caches between tests (e.g., `clearPluginHostRuntimeState()`, `clearPluginMetadataLifecycleCaches()`). However, the `registeredChannelPluginLookup` module-level cache in `registry-lookup.ts` was not cleared. When one test loaded channel plugin registrations into the lookup cache, subsequent tests that called `listRegisteredChannelPluginEntries()`, `findRegisteredChannelPluginEntry()`, or `normalizeAnyChannelId()` saw stale cached channel entries from the previous test — even though the active registry itself had already been reset. This caused flaky test behavior in CI. Fixes #92094.\r\n\r\n## Approach\r\n\r\nExport `resetRegisteredChannelPluginLookupCache()` from `src/channels/registry-lookup.ts` and call it from `resetPluginRuntimeStateForTest()` in `src/plugins/runtime.ts`, completing the singleton-clear pattern established by `clearPluginHostRuntimeState()` and `clearPluginMetadataLifecycleCaches()`. No behavioral changes — only test-isolation hygiene.\r\n\r\n## Real behavior proof\r\n\r\nWrote a reproduction script that simulates two sequential tests sharing the same process:\r\n\r\n1. **Test A** calls `setActivePluginRegistry()` with `telegram` and `discord` channels, then calls `listRegisteredChannelPluginEntries()` — the module-level `registeredChannelPluginLookup` cache is populated.\r\n2. **Test B** calls `resetPluginRuntimeStateForTest()` (which previously did NOT clear the lookup cache) followed by `setActivePluginRegistry()` with `slack` only.\r\n3. Test B then calls `listRegisteredChannelPluginEntries()` and `findRegisteredChannelPluginEntry(\"telegram\")`.\r\n\r\n**Before the fix:** `findRegisteredChannelPluginEntry(\"telegram\")` returns the telegram entry from Test A's stale cache — even though the active registry has no telegram channel. This is the false-positive bleed.\r\n\r\n**After the fix:** `resetRegisteredChannelPluginLookupCache()` is called inside `resetPluginRuntimeStateForTest()`, so the stale cache is discarded. `findRegisteredChannelPluginEntry(\"telegram\")` correctly returns `undefined` after Test B's reset.\r\n\r\n## Evidence after fix\r\n\r\n```bash\r\npnpm exec vitest run src/channels/registry.helpers.test.ts\r\npnpm exec vitest run src/agents/simple-completion-runtime.test.ts\r\npnpm exec vitest run --config test/vitest/vitest.agents-core.config.ts\r\n```\r\n\r\n Test Files  38 passed (38)\r\n      Tests  941 passed (941)\r\n   Start at  16:38:10\r\n   Duration  28.43s\r\n\r\nAll 941 tests pass. The simple-completion-runtime.test.ts tests that previously needed extra mockReset() boilerplate now rely on proper test isolation through resetPluginRuntimeStateForTest().\r\n\r\nWhat was not tested\r\nLive daemon with actual channel plugins (requires external credentials and network access)\r\nCross-process or multi-worker test scenarios where the module-level cache lives in separate VM contexts\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n",
